WEBVTT

00:09.487 --> 00:11.446
-MITCH: ANYWAY, I WAS
JUST CLOSING MY TOWER.

00:11.968 --> 00:13.143
THERE THEY WERE.

00:13.274 --> 00:14.971
FIVE OR SIX OF THESE GUYS,

00:15.102 --> 00:18.192
HOUNDING DOWN BEERS,
STARTIN' BONFIRES.

00:18.322 --> 00:20.542
I MEAN, THESE GUYS
WERE BAD DUDES.

00:20.672 --> 00:21.891
GANG BANGERS.

00:22.413 --> 00:23.327
-DID YOU CALL FOR BACKUP?

00:23.458 --> 00:24.415
-WHY?

00:24.546 --> 00:25.721
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

00:25.851 --> 00:27.244
-TOUCHY!

00:27.375 --> 00:28.202
I WAS JUST SUGGESTING
YOU MIGHT'VE BEEN

00:28.332 --> 00:29.290
A LITTLE OUTNUMBERED.

00:29.420 --> 00:30.943
-NEWMIE, I HAVE A BLACK BELT

00:31.074 --> 00:33.772
IN THE STRONGEST OF
ALL WEAPONS, WORDS.

00:33.903 --> 00:35.905
ANYWAY, EIGHT OR
NINE OF THESE GUYS--

00:36.036 --> 00:37.211
-I THOUGHT IT WAS FIVE OR SIX.

00:37.341 --> 00:38.386
-YOU WANNA HEAR
THE STORY OR NOT?

00:38.516 --> 00:39.648
-PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME BEG,

00:39.778 --> 00:40.562
OH MIGHTY WARRIOR.

00:40.692 --> 00:42.129
-OK, FORGET IT.

00:42.651 --> 00:44.392
BUT THEY DID NOT INTIMIDATE ME.

00:44.522 --> 00:46.568
-OH I BELIEVE THEY
DIDN'T INTIMIDATE YOU.

00:46.698 --> 00:47.786
I JUST FIND IT HARD TO BELIEVE

00:47.917 --> 00:49.266
THEY DIDN'T BEAT YOU TO A PULP.

00:49.397 --> 00:50.615
THEY'LL BE BACK, YOU KNOW.

00:50.746 --> 00:52.791
-NO NO NO, THEY
LEFT AND BELIEVE ME,

00:52.922 --> 00:54.271
THEY WILL NOT MESS
WITH ME AGAIN.

00:54.402 --> 00:55.359
-RIGHT.

01:10.940 --> 01:14.074
NO. THEY AREN'T GONNA
MESS WITH YOU AGAIN.

01:24.301 --> 01:27.870
♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

01:28.000 --> 01:31.700
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

01:31.830 --> 01:35.747
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

01:35.878 --> 01:39.490
♪ WHEN THE EDGE OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

01:39.621 --> 01:42.363
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

01:42.493 --> 01:44.582
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT

01:47.846 --> 01:49.413
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:49.544 --> 01:53.809
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:56.812 --> 01:58.944
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:59.075 --> 02:00.424
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:00.555 --> 02:02.731
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR

02:02.861 --> 02:04.646
♪ OH DON'T YOU FEAR

02:04.776 --> 02:07.823
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:07.953 --> 02:10.651
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

02:10.782 --> 02:14.134
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:26.494 --> 02:27.712
[GRUNTING]

02:30.715 --> 02:32.543
-MAN, I HATE THIS!

02:32.674 --> 02:33.718
-WHY, GARCIA?

02:34.241 --> 02:35.329
PAY'S GOOD.

02:35.894 --> 02:37.853
YOU GET TO WORK
IN THE GREAT OUTDOORS

02:37.983 --> 02:39.594
WITH THE FRESH AIR.

02:41.291 --> 02:42.640
IT'S A REAL OPPORTUNITY FOR YOU

02:42.771 --> 02:44.512
TO ADVANCE UP THAT
CORPORATE LADDER.

02:46.905 --> 02:48.820
-YOU'RE LOCO FROM THE SUN,
DEKE, YOU KNOW THAT?

02:49.386 --> 02:51.693
-OH MAN, IT'S, IT'S
ATTITUDE, GARCIA.

02:52.215 --> 02:54.391
LIFE GIVES YOU LEMONS,
YOU MAKE LEMONADE.

02:55.262 --> 02:56.480
I LOVE LEMONADE!

03:01.833 --> 03:03.661
-OBSERVATION DAY?

03:03.792 --> 03:05.924
SO I WHAT? OBSERVE?

03:06.447 --> 03:08.884
-YOU STUDY EVERYTHING
THE LIFEGUARDS DO.

03:09.014 --> 03:10.668
HOW THEY WATCH THEIR WATER,

03:10.799 --> 03:11.974
HOW THEY TALK TO EACH OTHER

03:12.104 --> 03:14.759
BY SWINGING THE RESCUE CANS.

03:14.890 --> 03:16.500
IT'S GONNA BE YOUR
TURN SOON ENOUGH,

03:16.631 --> 03:17.806
AND I WANT YOU TO BE READY.

03:18.937 --> 03:19.982
-JESSIE: YEAH.

03:22.767 --> 03:24.247
-DON'T WORRY.

03:24.378 --> 03:26.031
THEY'RE PRISONERS FROM
THE MALIBU WORK CAMP.

03:26.162 --> 03:27.816
THEY SEND 'EM IN TO CLEAN
UP THE LITTER ON THE BEACH.

03:39.001 --> 03:40.524
-HOW ABOUT RIGHT HERE,
THIS ONE.

03:44.789 --> 03:46.138
HI!

03:47.357 --> 03:48.532
IT'S A GREAT DAY!

03:49.446 --> 03:51.318
YOU'VE GOT THE GREATEST JOB!

03:51.448 --> 03:53.494
-IT'S THE BEST
OFFICE IN THE WORLD!

03:53.624 --> 03:54.495
YOU FOLKS FROM OUT OF TOWN?

03:54.625 --> 03:55.974
-HOW CAN YOU TELL?

03:56.105 --> 03:57.498
-I NOTICED THE HAT.

03:57.628 --> 03:58.673
UTAH JAZZ.

03:58.803 --> 04:00.718
-SALT LAKE CITY,
WE'RE ON VACATION.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.678
-COME HON, LET'S HIT THE WATER.

04:03.808 --> 04:05.157
-NO NO, I'M GONNA PAINT.

04:05.288 --> 04:05.897
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE
THE MORNING LIGHT.

04:06.028 --> 04:07.072
GO ON, GO AHEAD.

04:16.690 --> 04:18.040
-HOW LONG YOU IN TOWN FOR?

04:18.562 --> 04:21.216
-TWO GLORIOUS,
SUN-FILLED WEEKS.

04:21.738 --> 04:23.698
I BUGGED VIC UNTIL
HE FINALLY CAVED IN

04:23.828 --> 04:26.091
AND HE BROUGHT ME
SOMEWHERE I COULD THAW OUT.

04:27.223 --> 04:28.224
[GRUNTING]

04:36.101 --> 04:37.799
-HEY, HEY!

04:37.929 --> 04:39.540
THE SURF'S BEEN GETTING A
LITTLE BIGGER THE LAST HOUR.

04:39.670 --> 04:41.019
MAYBE YOU WANT TO WAIT
'TIL THE SETS GET SMALLER.

04:41.150 --> 04:42.456
-NO, NO, I'M OK, REALLY, I SWIM,

04:42.586 --> 04:44.501
I SWIM EVERY DAY
AT THE Y BACK HOME.

04:44.632 --> 04:46.286
-WELL, A POOL'S A LITTLE
DIFFERENT THAN THE OCEAN.

04:46.416 --> 04:48.026
-I'M OK IN THE WATER.
I'M VIC, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

04:48.157 --> 04:49.724
-APRIL. APRIL GIMINSKI.

04:49.854 --> 04:50.855
-WELL, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT ME, APRIL.

04:50.986 --> 04:51.856
NO SWEAT, I PROMISE.

04:51.987 --> 04:53.771
-ALL RIGHT.

04:53.902 --> 04:54.598
-HEY APRIL, CAN
YOU DO ME A FAVOR?
-APRIL: WHAT?

04:54.729 --> 04:56.426
-VIC: WOULD YOU HOLD THIS?

04:56.557 --> 04:57.122
I DON'T WANT TO
LOSE IT OUT THERE.
-SURE.

04:57.862 --> 04:58.646
WHAT ABOUT YOUR NECKLACE?

04:58.776 --> 05:00.256
-OH, ST. CHRISTOPHER, OH NO, I,

05:00.387 --> 05:01.736
I NEVER TAKE IT OFF.

05:01.866 --> 05:03.651
-HEY, IF YOU GET
TIRED, COME ON IN, OK?

05:13.095 --> 05:14.836
-HE'S JUST A BIG KID.

05:14.966 --> 05:16.838
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
HE HAS EVER SEEN THE OCEAN

05:16.968 --> 05:18.579
IN HIS WHOLE LIFE.

05:18.709 --> 05:20.407
HE COULDN'T SLEEP LAST NIGHT
JUST THINKING ABOUT IT.

05:24.715 --> 05:25.803
[GRUNTING]

05:28.937 --> 05:30.852
-GO INTO MY TOWER AND TAKE
THE PHONE OFF THE HOOK.

05:30.982 --> 05:31.896
-WHAT? WHAT?

05:32.027 --> 05:32.810
-HURRY!
-SHERRI: OK!

05:51.002 --> 05:55.659
[SIRENS BLARING]

06:16.898 --> 06:18.029
-OK!

06:18.900 --> 06:20.771
OK! HANG ON!

06:34.219 --> 06:35.612
CAN YOU KICK?

06:35.743 --> 06:37.571
THEN I NEED YOUR HELP, OK?

06:41.749 --> 06:42.576
[GRUNTING]

06:47.407 --> 06:48.843
YOU CAN'T PULL ME!

06:48.973 --> 06:49.887
HOLD ON!

07:16.218 --> 07:17.219
VIC!

07:29.666 --> 07:31.668
[SIREN BLARING]

07:43.506 --> 07:49.207
[SIREN BLARING]

07:53.037 --> 07:54.256
-SHERRI: VIC!

07:55.692 --> 07:56.606
VIC!

08:01.176 --> 08:02.438
-YOU GUYS, LET'S GO AHEAD!

08:02.569 --> 08:03.744
THEY'RE AT THE CODE THREE.

08:05.093 --> 08:06.007
-YOU ALL RIGHT?

08:06.137 --> 08:07.182
WHAT HAPPENED?

08:07.835 --> 08:08.749
-HE WAS BODY SURFING.

08:08.879 --> 08:10.272
-IS IT A GUY OR A GIRL?
-GUY.

08:10.402 --> 08:11.578
-HOW OLD?

08:11.708 --> 08:13.580
-UM, EARLY 20'S, I GUESS.

08:13.710 --> 08:15.233
-ALL RIGHT,
HOOK UP WITH BURNETT
AND JOHN, START A GRID SEARCH.

08:15.364 --> 08:16.408
-WE'RE ON IT!

08:16.974 --> 08:18.933
-SHERRI: VIC! VIC!

08:19.063 --> 08:20.891
-NO NO NO NO NO, I
DON'T WANT YOU OUT THERE.

08:21.022 --> 08:21.892
-I GOTTA HELP, MITCH!

08:22.023 --> 08:22.937
-YOU'RE IN NO CONDITION,

08:23.067 --> 08:24.678
I WANT YOU TO GO TO THE TRUCKS.

08:24.808 --> 08:25.679
JUST GO TO THE TRUCK,
WE'LL HANDLE THIS.

08:28.203 --> 08:29.726
-I CAN'T JUST--

08:29.857 --> 08:31.511
-I TOLD YOU, I DON'T WANT
YOU OUT THERE ANYMORE.

08:32.076 --> 08:33.034
-I HAVE TO TALK TO HER.

08:33.164 --> 08:34.688
-WHO?
-HIS WIFE.

08:34.818 --> 08:36.254
-ALEX, TAKE HER
BACK TO HEADQUARTERS,

08:36.385 --> 08:37.691
I DON'T WANT HER TALKING
TO THE VICTIM'S WIFE.

08:37.821 --> 08:38.561
-OK, COME ON, I'M
BUYING COFFEE, LET'S GO.

08:38.692 --> 08:39.475
-I DON'T WANT TO!

08:39.606 --> 08:40.345
IT'S MY RESPONSIBILITY--

08:40.476 --> 08:42.086
-NOW! GO!

08:42.217 --> 08:43.827
-SHERRI: VIC!

08:49.572 --> 08:50.530
-EXCUSE ME.

08:51.095 --> 08:52.140
LIEUTENANT MITCH BUCHANNON,

08:52.270 --> 08:53.794
LA COUNTY LIFEGUARDS.

08:53.924 --> 08:55.926
I'M THE LIFEGUARD IN
CHARGE OF THE RESCUE.

08:56.057 --> 08:57.014
I UNDERSTAND YOUR HUSBAND--

08:57.145 --> 08:58.712
-HE'S OUT THERE.

08:58.842 --> 08:59.974
-CAN YOU TELL ME THE COLOR
OF HIS SWIMMING TRUNKS?

09:00.104 --> 09:03.151
-OH UM, BLUE WITH
LITTLE SAILBOATS ON THEM.

09:03.281 --> 09:05.022
BUT HE'S A REALLY GOOD SWIMMER.

09:05.153 --> 09:06.154
-OK, IT'S FINE.

09:06.284 --> 09:07.721
WAS HE TAKING ANY MEDICATION

09:07.851 --> 09:09.549
OR DRINKING BEFORE
HE WENT IN THE WATER?

09:09.679 --> 09:10.898
-NO.

09:11.942 --> 09:13.857
WHY CAN'T YOU JUST BRING HIM IN?

09:13.988 --> 09:15.424
-UH, WE'RE DOING
THE BEST WE CAN.

09:15.555 --> 09:17.078
IN THE MEANTIME, I
THINK IT'S BEST FOR YOU

09:17.208 --> 09:18.601
IF YOU GO WITH ONE
OF OUR LIFEGUARDS.

09:22.344 --> 09:23.563
-VIC!

09:23.693 --> 09:24.564
VIC!

09:31.179 --> 09:32.528
VIC!

09:34.399 --> 09:35.836
VIC!

09:39.100 --> 09:40.405
HONEY!

09:42.103 --> 09:44.453
VIC, PLEASE!

09:45.759 --> 09:46.716
VIC!

09:48.805 --> 09:52.243
[SHOWER RUNNING]

09:55.290 --> 09:59.860
[SOBBING]

10:39.073 --> 10:40.944
-IT'S MY FAULT!

10:41.075 --> 10:43.207
-NO, IT IS NOT YOUR FAULT.

10:45.340 --> 10:46.776
-I HAD HIM.

10:46.907 --> 10:49.431
-YOU DID EVERYTHING
YOU COULD, APRIL.

10:51.955 --> 10:54.218
-THEN WHY ISN'T HE HERE?

10:57.178 --> 10:58.701
I LOST HIM!

10:58.832 --> 11:00.660
-SHH, SHH.

11:06.753 --> 11:10.539
[TENSE MUSIC]

11:19.156 --> 11:20.288
-YEAH, IT'S BUCHANNON.

11:20.418 --> 11:22.072
WE'RE LOSING THE LIGHT.

11:22.203 --> 11:23.900
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA
CALL OFF THE SEARCH.

11:24.031 --> 11:26.163
I WANT EVERY AVAILABLE LIFEGUARD
BACK HERE TOMORROW MORNING

11:26.294 --> 11:27.687
AT OH FIVE THIRTY.

11:28.513 --> 11:29.906
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:30.037 --> 11:31.778
-LOOK, WE'VE USED EVERY
PIECE OF EQUIPMENT,

11:31.908 --> 11:33.954
EVERY SINGLE LIFEGUARD
WE HAVE ACCESS TO.

11:34.084 --> 11:35.303
THERE'S STILL NO
SIGN OF YOUR HUSBAND.

11:35.433 --> 11:38.088
-HE'S OUT THERE, I SAW HIM.

11:38.219 --> 11:39.481
-WE'RE STILL GONNA LOOK,
BUT NOT TONIGHT,

11:39.611 --> 11:40.438
TOMORROW MORNING.

11:40.569 --> 11:42.527
-NO, HE'S JUST MISSING!

11:42.658 --> 11:44.181
YOU'VE GOT TO FIND HIM.

11:44.312 --> 11:45.226
I LOVE HIM, I NEED HIM!
-SHERRI, HE'S BEEN MISSING

11:45.356 --> 11:46.923
SINCE THIS MORNING.

11:47.054 --> 11:48.272
HE'S BEEN IN THE
WATER FOR HOURS.

11:48.403 --> 11:50.797
-MAYBE HE GOT PULLED BY
ONE OF THOSE CURRENTS.

11:50.927 --> 11:52.668
-OK, OK, HE MIGHT
HAVE BEEN PULLED

11:52.799 --> 11:53.800
BY ONE OF THE CURRENTS,

11:53.930 --> 11:55.497
THEY WERE REALLY STRONG TODAY.

11:55.627 --> 11:56.977
-OK, MAYBE, MAYBE IT
DRAGGED HIM DOWN THE BEACH,

11:57.107 --> 11:58.326
DOWN THE COAST.

11:59.066 --> 12:00.937
MAYBE HE SWAM TO
SHORE WAY DOWN THERE,

12:01.068 --> 12:02.722
AND, AND HE'S JUST RESTING NOW,

12:02.852 --> 12:06.464
OR MAYBE SOME BOAT CAME
BY AND PICKED HIM UP OR--

12:06.595 --> 12:07.944
-YOU KNOW, IT'S GETTING
REALLY COLD, LOOK.

12:08.075 --> 12:09.772
-SHERRI: OR MAYBE,
MAYBE HE HIT HIS HEAD

12:09.903 --> 12:11.556
ON THESE JETTY ROCKS AND--
-WHY DON'T YOU PUT THIS ON?

12:11.687 --> 12:14.081
-AND HE'S, AND GOT STUNNED
OR MAYBE HE GOT AMNESIA, OR.

12:15.082 --> 12:16.431
-LISTEN, OK.
-YOU KNOW,

12:16.561 --> 12:17.780
HE DOESN'T HAVE HIS
WALLET, SO MAYBE,

12:17.911 --> 12:19.477
MAYBE HE'S HITCHHIKING
TO THE HOTEL

12:19.608 --> 12:21.044
OR MAYBE HE'S WALKING.
-I TELL YOU WHAT.

12:21.175 --> 12:22.785
WE'RE GONNA GO BACK
TO HEADQUARTERS, OK?

12:22.916 --> 12:24.352
GET YOU A CUP OF COFFEE

12:24.482 --> 12:26.180
AND I PROMISE WE'LL TALK
ABOUT THIS, ALL RIGHT?

12:26.310 --> 12:28.660
-YOU KNOW, I BROUGHT MY CELL
PHONE JUST IN CASE HE CALLS.

12:28.791 --> 12:30.488
-IT'S A GOOD IDEA,
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

12:30.619 --> 12:34.928
-SHERRI, HIS WIFE, PAINTED
WHILE HE WENT BODY SURFING.

12:36.407 --> 12:37.757
-HOW'D HE GET IN TROUBLE?

12:39.584 --> 12:41.238
-THE SURF WAS REALLY BIG.

12:41.761 --> 12:43.501
AND I WARNED HIM, BUT...

12:44.415 --> 12:46.026
HE SAID HE WAS
GOOD IN THE WATER.

12:48.202 --> 12:49.769
I SHOULD'VE MADE HIM GET OUT.

12:52.423 --> 12:54.599
HE GOT SLAMMED BY A
COUPLE OF BIG WAVES

12:54.730 --> 12:56.776
AND HE WENT UNDER.

12:59.213 --> 13:01.345
THE SURF WAS SO STRONG, I,

13:01.476 --> 13:03.826
I HAD TROUBLE GETTING
TO HIM, BUT I DID.

13:04.914 --> 13:06.568
-ALEX: WHAT WAS
YOUR PLAN OF RESCUE?

13:08.396 --> 13:11.094
-I KNEW THAT BACKUP WAS
AT LEAST FIVE MINUTES AWAY,

13:11.225 --> 13:13.140
AND THERE WAS NO
ONE ON DUTY YET.

13:14.358 --> 13:17.666
BUT I WAS SO TIRED AND I KNEW

13:17.797 --> 13:19.189
THAT THE ONLY SHOT THAT WE HAD

13:19.320 --> 13:21.496
WAS IF WE MADE IT
THROUGH THE DROP ZONE

13:21.626 --> 13:22.802
AND SWAM TO SHORE.

13:25.848 --> 13:27.937
BUT THIS HUGE WAVE CAME,

13:29.199 --> 13:30.810
AND IT TUMBLE DRIED US.

13:32.376 --> 13:33.943
THE IMPACT WA--

13:34.465 --> 13:35.771
I LOST MY GRIP ON HIM.

13:36.903 --> 13:39.775
I WENT DOWN AND I
KEPT DIVING AND DIVING

13:39.906 --> 13:40.820
LOOKING FOR HIM.

13:41.472 --> 13:42.647
BUT IT...

13:43.605 --> 13:46.042
-APRIL, YOU'RE GONNA BE OK.

13:46.173 --> 13:48.697
-I'M FINE, I SWEAR, I JUST...

13:51.569 --> 13:53.484
-LOOK APRIL, I THINK
IT MAY BE A GOOD IDEA

13:53.615 --> 13:55.269
IF YOU TOOK SOME
TIME OFF, YOU KNOW?

13:56.009 --> 13:57.619
MAYBE GET SOME COUNSELING.

14:23.384 --> 14:24.341
APRIL.

14:25.299 --> 14:26.300
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

14:27.431 --> 14:28.606
-THIS IS HIS ROOM KEY,

14:28.737 --> 14:29.694
AND HE ASKED ME TO HOLD IT,

14:29.825 --> 14:30.652
I, I SHOULD GIVE IT--

14:30.782 --> 14:31.696
-HERE.

14:32.610 --> 14:34.177
UH, NEWMAN?

14:34.308 --> 14:36.266
WILL YOU GIVE THIS
TO HER, PLEASE?

14:36.397 --> 14:37.224
-NEWMIE: SURE THING.

14:37.354 --> 14:38.312
-THANKS.

14:43.360 --> 14:45.014
LOOK, IT'S NOT
GONNA DO YOU OR HER

14:45.145 --> 14:46.624
ANY GOOD TO HOOK UP RIGHT NOW.

14:54.284 --> 14:56.156
WHY DON'T I JUST TAKE
YOU HOME, ALL RIGHT?

15:15.001 --> 15:16.916
-HONEY? BABE?

15:23.270 --> 15:24.836
I REALLY THOUGHT.

15:28.405 --> 15:29.363
OH.

15:29.972 --> 15:31.495
THANK YOU FOR YOUR JACKET.

15:31.626 --> 15:32.714
-NO, NO PROBLEM.

15:32.844 --> 15:33.933
HERE'S YOUR KEY.

15:34.716 --> 15:37.371
AND I PROMISE, WE RESUME
THE SEARCH TOMORROW MORNING.

15:37.893 --> 15:39.286
IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN GET YOU NOW?

15:39.416 --> 15:42.898
-NO, I, I THINK I'M
GONNA SIT BY THE PHONE

15:43.029 --> 15:44.073
IN CASE HE CALLS.

15:44.204 --> 15:45.118
-OK.

15:46.032 --> 15:47.642
-TONIGHT WAS GONNA
BE OUR BIG NIGHT.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.298
A BIG SURPRISE.

15:53.822 --> 15:55.606
I WAS GONNA TELL
HIM I'M PREGNANT.

16:14.886 --> 16:16.279
YOU HAVE ANY KIDS, MITCH?

16:16.410 --> 16:18.803
-YEAH, YEAH I HAVE A SON.

16:19.369 --> 16:20.196
HOBIE.

16:21.110 --> 16:22.416
HE'S PRETTY MUCH A MAN NOW.

16:23.721 --> 16:25.114
-I CAN'T WAIT.

16:26.202 --> 16:27.943
WE'VE BEEN TRYING FOR SO LONG.

16:29.162 --> 16:31.816
VIC IS GONNA BE THE BEST
DADDY IN THE WHOLE WORLD.

16:33.688 --> 16:35.429
[PHONE RINGING]

16:37.474 --> 16:38.606
HONEY?

16:40.477 --> 16:41.435
NO.

16:42.218 --> 16:43.306
THANK YOU.

16:43.437 --> 16:45.178
YOU CAN CANCEL THE RESERVATION.

16:50.618 --> 16:53.621
WE WERE GONNA HAVE DINNER
IN THE HOTEL RESTAURANT.

16:54.665 --> 16:56.102
-UM, YOU HUNGRY?

16:56.232 --> 16:58.017
I COULD ORDER YOU ROOM SERVICE.

16:59.322 --> 17:00.454
-I'M OK.

17:00.584 --> 17:02.021
I'M REALLY NOT HUNGRY.

17:11.638 --> 17:15.859
[CHATTERING]

17:18.079 --> 17:19.733
-FILE THIS MISSING PERSONS
REPORT FOR ME, WILL YOU?

17:19.864 --> 17:20.909
THANKS.

17:21.692 --> 17:22.867
-HEY, WHAT CAN I DO TO HELP?

17:22.998 --> 17:25.435
-WELL, I'VE CONSOLIDATED
ALL THE MANPOWER HERE.

17:25.566 --> 17:27.002
TELL YOU WHAT.

17:27.133 --> 17:27.915
TAKE THIS RADIO,

17:28.047 --> 17:29.483
PATROL NORTH OF THE PIER.

17:29.613 --> 17:30.223
YOU SEE ANYTHING, CALL IT IN.

17:30.353 --> 17:31.485
-ALL RIGHT, YOU GOT IT.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.247
-YOU OK, JESSIE?

17:54.377 --> 17:55.248
-HUH?

17:56.075 --> 17:58.120
ME? YEAH, FINE.

18:03.473 --> 18:04.822
-LOUDSPEAKER: [MUMBLES] ZUMA,

18:04.953 --> 18:07.086
NORTH TO YOUR ORIGINAL LOCATION.

18:13.309 --> 18:15.572
-KELLY, CHECK NORTH OF THE
JETTY FOR ME, WOULD YOU?

18:17.835 --> 18:18.662
-MITCH?

18:18.793 --> 18:19.663
-HEY.

18:19.794 --> 18:20.969
GOOD MORNING.

18:21.100 --> 18:22.797
-ALEX: HOW LONG'S
SHE BEEN HERE?

18:22.927 --> 18:23.928
-I DON'T KNOW.

18:24.842 --> 18:27.323
I GOT HERE AT FIRST LIGHT,
SHE WAS ALREADY HERE.

18:28.890 --> 18:30.457
-WHY THE FULL SEARCH?

18:30.587 --> 18:32.850
IT SHOULD BE A BODY
RECOVERY OPERATION.

18:32.981 --> 18:34.896
-I KNOW, I KNOW,
I PROMISED HER.

18:35.026 --> 18:37.942
ALSO CHECKED EVERY HOSPITAL
10 MILES NORTH OF THE PIER,

18:38.073 --> 18:39.161
AND 10 MILES SOUTH.

18:39.683 --> 18:41.120
SANTA MONICA POLICE DEPARTMENT,

18:41.250 --> 18:42.469
THE VENICE POLICE DEPARTMENT--

18:42.599 --> 18:43.644
-MITCH.

18:44.297 --> 18:46.777
DON'T YOU THINK YOU'RE
GETTING A LITTLE INVOLVED?

19:15.589 --> 19:16.938
-OFFICER: ALL RIGHT, NEXT LEG.

19:20.115 --> 19:20.985
GOOD, OK, MOVE ON.

19:21.116 --> 19:21.986
NEXT!

19:24.119 --> 19:25.425
RIGHT LEG, LET'S GO.

19:30.865 --> 19:31.866
-ALL RIGHT, HERE WE GO.

19:34.173 --> 19:35.739
-OH GARCIA, YOU ALL
RIGHT, MAN, YOU ALL RIGHT?

19:35.870 --> 19:36.871
-GARCIA: MY STOMACH, MAN!

19:37.001 --> 19:38.002
-WHAT'S WRONG WITH GARCIA?

19:38.133 --> 19:39.395
-I DON'T KNOW, MAN. SOMETHING IN HIS GUT,

19:39.526 --> 19:41.049
MUST BE FOOD POISONING
OR SOMETHING.

19:43.486 --> 19:44.966
KEYS, GET THE KEYS!

20:00.329 --> 20:01.765
-OFFICER: WE GOT TWO LOOSE!

20:12.863 --> 20:14.082
GET 'EM!

20:15.039 --> 20:16.302
HEAD 'EM OFF!

20:17.128 --> 20:18.304
CUT 'EM OFF!

20:20.131 --> 20:21.611
-OFFICER: I GOT
'EM FROM THIS SIDE!

20:23.047 --> 20:28.096
[EXCITING MUSIC]

20:57.908 --> 21:00.084
[GRUNTING]

21:03.914 --> 21:06.221
-HOLY SMOKES, THEY WENT OVER!

21:17.537 --> 21:18.886
WHERE ARE THEY?

21:19.016 --> 21:20.061
-YOU SEE 'EM?

21:20.191 --> 21:22.063
-DISPATCH, THIS IS MOBILE TWO.

21:22.193 --> 21:24.239
WE'VE GOT TWO RABBITS IN THE
WATER, REQUEST BACKUP, OVER.

21:25.936 --> 21:27.547
-CB RADIO: 95201,
COME IN, 201.

21:28.330 --> 21:31.246
-YEAH, 295, THIS IS
201, SEND YOUR TRAFFIC.

21:31.377 --> 21:33.248
-CB RADIO: TWO CONVICTS
ESCAPED FROM VENICE BEACH

21:33.379 --> 21:34.380
ON WORK DETAIL.

21:34.510 --> 21:35.337
WE'RE CLOSING DOWN THE BEACH.

21:56.793 --> 21:57.968
-HEY, JESS.

22:00.841 --> 22:02.146
LONG TIME, BABY.

22:12.200 --> 22:13.462
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN HERE?

22:14.202 --> 22:15.812
-MAKING LEMONADE, BABY.

22:16.987 --> 22:18.337
-DEKE, THEY'RE GONNA CATCH YOU.

22:18.467 --> 22:18.946
YOU'VE GOTTA GO AND
TURN YOURSELF IN.

22:19.076 --> 22:20.339
-NO WAY!

22:20.469 --> 22:21.731
BESIDES, I DON'T
PARTICULARLY CARE

22:21.862 --> 22:23.342
FOR THE ACCOMMODATIONS
AT THE CAMP.

22:23.472 --> 22:25.909
AND THEY JUST FLAT OUT
REFUSED TO UPGRADE MY ROOM,

22:26.040 --> 22:28.956
SO I'VE JUST TAKEN IT
UPON MYSELF TO CHECK OUT.

22:30.566 --> 22:31.698
-WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

22:32.394 --> 22:33.482
-I'M HEADING SOUTH.

22:34.004 --> 22:35.658
MEXICO'S NICE THIS TIME OF YEAR.

22:35.789 --> 22:38.095
-MEXICO? HOW?

22:38.226 --> 22:39.445
-REMEMBER BUZZ?

22:40.489 --> 22:42.143
HE'S GOT A FISHING BOAT.

22:42.273 --> 22:43.710
I FIGURE THAT UH,

22:44.319 --> 22:46.234
WE JUST SET SAIL DUE SOUTH

22:46.365 --> 22:50.543
AND THEN IT'S SOMBREROS,
MARGARITAS, OLE.

22:51.500 --> 22:52.936
-NO, DEKE, I CAN'T.

22:53.067 --> 22:54.111
I WON'T.

22:54.242 --> 22:56.244
-YES, BABY YOU CAN, YOU CAN.

22:56.853 --> 22:58.681
-I MADE THAT MISTAKE ONCE.

22:59.203 --> 23:00.596
I'M NOT GONNA DO IT AGAIN.

23:02.685 --> 23:04.295
-ALEX: HEY JESSIE!

23:05.558 --> 23:06.559
JESSIE!

23:10.214 --> 23:12.478
-ALL THERE IS TO IT,
IS TO DO IT, BABY.

23:13.566 --> 23:14.610
-JESSIE!

23:14.741 --> 23:16.003
HEY WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

23:16.133 --> 23:18.353
THAT TOWER'S CLOSED FOR REPAIRS.

23:19.006 --> 23:21.051
-YEAH, ONE SEC.

23:21.182 --> 23:22.444
-SURE.

23:32.106 --> 23:34.325
HEY WE GOT A REPORT ON A
COUPLE OF ESCAPED CONVICTS,

23:34.456 --> 23:35.675
YOU SEE ANYTHING?
-ME?

23:36.371 --> 23:38.068
NO. NOTHIN'.

23:39.548 --> 23:40.723
-WHY DON'T YOU HOP IN,
I'LL GIVE YOU A RIDE.

23:40.854 --> 23:42.290
-THANKS.

23:55.825 --> 23:56.957
-HEY, JESSIE.

23:57.087 --> 23:57.914
-HEY.

23:58.045 --> 23:59.002
HOW YOU DOING?

23:59.133 --> 24:00.177
-GOOD!

24:00.308 --> 24:01.527
WANT SOME?
-NO, THANKS.

24:01.657 --> 24:03.050
HEY, DID YOU TALK TO APRIL?

24:03.180 --> 24:04.181
-YEAH.

24:04.312 --> 24:05.444
-JESSIE: HOW'S SHE DOIN'?

24:05.574 --> 24:07.184
-WELL, YOU KNOW,
IT TAKES A WHILE

24:07.315 --> 24:08.751
TO GET OVER LOSING A VICTIM.

24:08.882 --> 24:09.752
-YEAH.

24:11.406 --> 24:13.060
JUST HOPE THAT
NEVER HAPPENS TO ME.

24:13.190 --> 24:15.062
THAT'S IF I EVER
BECOME A LIFEGUARD.

24:15.192 --> 24:16.803
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "IF"?

24:16.933 --> 24:18.718
THEY'RE ALREADY CALLING
YOU "THE NATURAL."

24:18.848 --> 24:20.241
-HMM.

24:20.371 --> 24:21.416
-SOMETHING GO WRONG
IN ROOKIE SCHOOL?

24:22.156 --> 24:23.026
-NO.

24:23.157 --> 24:24.550
-THEN WHAT'S WRONG?

24:24.680 --> 24:25.899
I NOTICED YOU SEEMED
A LITTLE OFF TODAY.

24:27.335 --> 24:29.032
-HAVE YOU EVER
FELT STUCK, ALEX?

24:29.163 --> 24:30.207
-STUCK?

24:30.338 --> 24:31.644
-YEAH.

24:32.253 --> 24:33.254
LIKE YOU FEEL LIKE
HELPING SOMEONE

24:33.384 --> 24:34.211
EVEN WHEN YOU KNOW IT'S WRONG?

24:34.342 --> 24:35.517
-AH.

24:35.648 --> 24:36.866
THAT KINDA STUCK.

24:38.041 --> 24:38.912
-EVER FELT THAT WAY?

24:39.565 --> 24:41.001
-YEAH.

24:41.131 --> 24:43.525
I UH, I HAD THIS CRUSH
ON THIS GUY ONCE.

24:43.656 --> 24:46.180
I THOUGHT I WAS MADLY
IN LOVE WITH HIM.

24:46.310 --> 24:47.398
HE ASKED ME TO MARRY HIM,

24:47.529 --> 24:51.881
I ACCEPTED, AND THEN
I CALLED IT OFF.

24:52.012 --> 24:53.361
-WHY?

24:53.492 --> 24:54.623
-'CAUSE I KNEW IT
WOULD NEVER WORK.

24:54.754 --> 24:56.364
NO MATTER HOW BAD
I WANTED IT TO,

24:56.495 --> 24:58.497
IT JUST DIDN'T FEEL RIGHT.

24:59.454 --> 25:00.847
BUT I KEPT LOOKING DOWN

25:00.977 --> 25:03.066
AT THIS DIAMOND
RING ON MY FINGER

25:03.197 --> 25:05.721
AND I JUST FELT SO--

25:05.852 --> 25:07.767
-STUCK?
-YEAH.

25:10.639 --> 25:11.422
-WHAT ABOUT HIM?

25:11.553 --> 25:13.555
-WELL, I'M SURE I HURT HIM,

25:13.686 --> 25:15.949
BUT IF I HAD GONE AHEAD WITH IT,

25:16.079 --> 25:18.429
I WOULD'VE ENDED UP HURTING
BOTH OF US LATER ON, SO.

25:20.867 --> 25:22.477
WELL, LISTEN.

25:23.434 --> 25:24.740
I DON'T KNOW IF
ANY OF THAT HELPED,

25:24.871 --> 25:26.612
BUT I GOTTA GET GOIN'.

25:26.742 --> 25:28.570
MY SISTER FIXED ME
UP ON A BLIND DATE

25:28.701 --> 25:31.530
AND I GOTTA GO HOME AND HAVE
AN ANXIETY ATTACK FIRST.

25:33.183 --> 25:34.402
I HOPE YOU GET UNSTUCK.

25:34.968 --> 25:36.273
BYE.

25:36.404 --> 25:37.144
-THANKS, ALEX.
-ALEX: SEE YA LATER!

25:37.274 --> 25:38.188
-ALL RIGHT.

25:55.510 --> 25:56.729
-♪ LET'S TAKE IT

25:58.165 --> 25:59.383
♪ LET'S GO

26:01.081 --> 26:02.256
♪ LET'S TAKE IT

26:05.041 --> 26:07.217
♪ BEFORE YOU I'D SAY I WAS

26:07.348 --> 26:09.872
♪ A LITTLE GOLDEN CHILD

26:10.438 --> 26:12.745
♪ NEVER GOT MY FINGERS DIRTY ♪

26:12.875 --> 26:15.051
♪ NEVER GOT SO WILD

26:15.617 --> 26:17.880
♪ BEFORE YOU I'D NEVER DONE ♪

26:18.011 --> 26:20.535
♪ NO PETTY CRIME

26:20.666 --> 26:23.538
♪ BUT NOW I'VE BEEN INSIDE OF THE BIG
HOUSE ♪

26:23.669 --> 26:25.801
♪ AND I KNOW WHY

26:27.586 --> 26:28.674
♪ LET'S TAKE IT

26:29.849 --> 26:31.459
♪ LET'S GO

26:32.634 --> 26:34.201
♪ LET'S TAKE IT

26:36.551 --> 26:39.336
♪ YOU'RE A REAL BAD INFLUENCE

26:39.467 --> 26:41.600
♪ BUT I CAN'T GET ENOUGH

26:42.426 --> 26:44.820
♪ YOU MAKE ME WANNA TAKE A RIDE IN THE
CITY ♪

26:44.951 --> 26:46.953
♪ AND START TAKING STUFF

26:48.432 --> 26:50.173
♪ I DON'T WANNA GET LOCKED UP

26:50.696 --> 26:53.916
♪ BUT I CAN'T MAKE IT WITHOUT YOU ♪

26:58.355 --> 27:00.967
♪ YOU MAKE ME WANNA TAKE STUFF

27:01.707 --> 27:04.840
♪ BUT I DON'T WANNA TAKE IT WITHOUT YOU ♪

27:20.377 --> 27:22.423
♪ I DON'T WANNA GET LOCKED UP

27:22.553 --> 27:25.687
♪ BUT I CAN'T MAKE IT WITHOUT YOU

27:31.171 --> 27:32.955
♪ YOU MAKE ME WANNA TAKE STUFF

27:33.826 --> 27:36.742
♪ BUT I DON'T WANNA TAKE IT WITHOUT YOU ♪

27:42.443 --> 27:43.531
♪ LET'S TAKE IT

27:45.141 --> 27:46.055
♪ LET'S GO

27:47.622 --> 27:48.405
♪ LET'S TAKE IT

27:48.536 --> 27:51.278
[SIRENS BLARING]

28:02.376 --> 28:03.551
-HEY.

28:05.945 --> 28:07.686
I BROUGHT YOU SOME DRY CLOTHES.

28:09.296 --> 28:10.645
-THANKS, BABY, YOU DID GOOD.

28:15.563 --> 28:16.564
THAT LOOK IN YOUR EYE,

28:17.478 --> 28:18.479
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

28:20.046 --> 28:21.177
-ABOUT THE OLD DAYS.

28:23.658 --> 28:25.573
-YEAH, WELL IT'S GONNA
BE THE SAME WAY AGAIN

28:25.704 --> 28:26.617
DOWN IN MEXICO.

28:29.925 --> 28:31.971
YOU GONNA GET US TO BUZZ'S BOAT?

28:35.583 --> 28:37.193
GOSH, I MISSED THAT.

28:43.678 --> 28:45.419
-MEET ME ON THE
ROCKS AT THE POINT

28:45.549 --> 28:47.116
AT EIGHT O'CLOCK
TOMORROW MORNING.

28:47.247 --> 28:48.291
-ALL RIGHT.

28:58.171 --> 28:59.650
-I THOUGHT
THE UNDERWATER RECOVERY UNIT

28:59.781 --> 29:01.522
HAD AN ASSIGNMENT UP IN MALIBU.

29:02.349 --> 29:03.742
-IT DID.

29:03.872 --> 29:06.048
I UH, DIVERTED IT DOWN HERE
FOR A PRACTICE SESSION.

29:07.920 --> 29:10.226
-MITCH, HE HAS BEEN
MISSING FOR THREE DAYS.

29:10.357 --> 29:11.532
IF HE WAS OUT BY THE JETTY,

29:11.662 --> 29:12.794
HIS BODY WOULD'VE
COME UP BY NOW.

29:12.925 --> 29:15.014
-I KNOW, BUT LOOK AT HER.

29:15.144 --> 29:16.798
SHE'S STANDING ON THE BEACH
WAITING FOR HIM TO COME BACK.

29:18.408 --> 29:19.670
I PROMISED HER WE'D
DO EVERYTHING WE COULD

29:19.801 --> 29:21.237
TO HELP FIND HIM.

29:21.368 --> 29:23.326
-THIS IS A WASTE OF
TIME AND YOU KNOW IT.

29:23.457 --> 29:24.806
-I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP HER.

29:24.937 --> 29:26.765
-BY HELPING HER, YOU
ARE HURTING APRIL.

29:26.895 --> 29:28.941
LOOK, SHE NEEDS TO CLOSE
THE DOOR ON THIS THING,

29:29.071 --> 29:30.594
AND YOU ARE DELIBERATELY
KEEPING IT OPEN.

29:30.725 --> 29:32.292
-APRIL DIDN'T LOSE A HUSBAND.

29:32.422 --> 29:33.946
-NO, BUT SHERRI DID,

29:34.076 --> 29:35.295
AND SHE NEEDS TO KNOW

29:35.425 --> 29:36.600
THAT HE IS NOT GONNA
BE COMING BACK,

29:36.731 --> 29:38.298
THAT HE'S DROWNED,
THAT HE'S DEAD.

29:38.428 --> 29:41.605
-I CAN'T HELP IT, I
FEEL SORRY FOR HER.

29:43.477 --> 29:45.827
SHE TOLD ME YESTERDAY
THAT SHE'S PREGNANT.

29:45.958 --> 29:48.961
AND SHE NEVER HAD A CHANCE
TO TELL HER HUSBAND.

29:49.788 --> 29:51.572
I JUST CAN'T TURN
MY BACK ON HER.

29:51.702 --> 29:53.487
-YOU'RE TURNING
YOUR BACK ON APRIL.

29:53.617 --> 29:54.749
-I KNOW WHAT I'M
DOING HERE, OK?

29:54.880 --> 29:55.837
-I KNOW WHAT I'M DOING.

29:55.968 --> 29:56.925
-WELL, WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,

29:57.056 --> 29:58.057
I BEG TO DIFFER.

29:58.622 --> 30:00.537
-CB RADIO: 201 TO 295 COME IN.

30:01.451 --> 30:03.192
-295 TO 201, COME IN.

30:03.323 --> 30:05.847
-CB RADIO: THE PILOT OF A
CESSNA HEADING FOR CATALINA

30:05.978 --> 30:07.327
SAW A MAN CLINGING
TO A BELL BUOY

30:07.457 --> 30:09.459
JUST SOUTH OF DOCKWEILER BEACH.

30:09.590 --> 30:11.505
-IT'S BEEN THREE
DAYS, 12 MILES,

30:11.635 --> 30:12.811
IT'S A MILLION TO ONE SHOT.

30:37.705 --> 30:39.446
-DEKE: I KNEW YOU'D
PULL THROUGH FOR ME, BABY.

30:39.576 --> 30:41.013
-JUMP ON!

30:41.143 --> 30:42.753
-DEKE: YOU AND ME ARE
MADE FOR EACH OTHER!

30:54.069 --> 30:55.636
-MITCH: THERE'S
SOMEBODY OUT THERE.

31:03.992 --> 31:07.517
[BELL CLANGING]

31:13.480 --> 31:15.047
-IT'S ONE OF THE
ESCAPED CONVICTS.

31:16.526 --> 31:17.745
SORRY, MITCH.

31:22.619 --> 31:25.361
-DEKE: WHOO! WE'RE FREE!

31:25.492 --> 31:27.320
YEAH!

31:28.277 --> 31:30.453
MEXICO!

31:35.067 --> 31:37.025
-COAST GUARD: BAYWATCH,
THIS IS THE COAST GUARD.

31:37.156 --> 31:38.070
WE LAUNCHED TO INTERCEPT.

31:38.200 --> 31:40.028
-JESS, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:40.594 --> 31:42.117
COME ON, TURN AROUND, LET'S GO!

31:42.248 --> 31:43.466
HURRY UP!
-NO.

31:43.597 --> 31:45.425
I'M NOT GOING TO
MEXICO WITH YOU, DEKE.

31:45.555 --> 31:47.122
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

31:47.253 --> 31:49.690
-LOOK, I'VE GOT SOMETHING
GOOD FOR ME HERE NOW,

31:49.820 --> 31:50.778
I'VE GOT A FUTURE.

31:50.909 --> 31:52.258
I'M NOT GONNA THROW IT AWAY.

31:53.912 --> 31:54.913
-NEWMIE: ROGER, COAST GUARD,

31:55.043 --> 31:55.957
WE'RE CLOSING IN FROM BEHIND.

31:56.088 --> 31:57.263
-GOD, JESS, YOU SET ME UP!

31:57.393 --> 31:58.525
[SCREAMING]

32:02.746 --> 32:07.708
[EXCITING MUSIC]

32:52.796 --> 32:54.407
-MAN ON RADIO: GROUP
LALB THIS IS POINTE BRIDGE.

32:54.537 --> 32:57.236
SUSPECT IS BEACHED AND IS
TRYING TO ESCAPE VIA THE CLIFF.

32:58.628 --> 33:00.282
-CB RADIO: ROGER,
POINT BRIDGE.

33:00.413 --> 33:01.544
WE'RE NOTIFYING THE LA
SHERIFF'S AND THE INTERSTATE.

33:28.702 --> 33:31.052
[GRUNTING]

33:38.320 --> 33:40.496
[GRUNTING]

33:46.415 --> 33:47.808
[PANTING]

33:47.938 --> 33:49.810
-DEKE: HELP! HELP ME!

33:49.940 --> 33:51.899
HELP! I CAN'T HANG ON!

34:01.517 --> 34:03.084
[GRUNTING]

34:13.442 --> 34:16.880
-PILOT: GROUP LALB,
THIS IS COAST GUARD 6518.

34:17.011 --> 34:19.621
ARRIVED ON THE SCENE AND ARE
EVALUATING THE SITUATION.

34:21.101 --> 34:22.886
-COMMENCE RESCUE CHECK,
PART TWO.

34:32.505 --> 34:35.072
-RESCUER: GROUP 6518,
MAN ON CLIFF IS IN TROUBLE.

34:35.203 --> 34:36.987
WE'RE PREPARING
FOR A CLIFF RESCUE.

34:50.391 --> 34:51.958
SWIMMER'S AT THE DOOR.

34:52.090 --> 34:54.657
SWIMMERS CONNECT AT RESCUE
CHECK PART TWO COMPLETE.

34:54.788 --> 34:56.355
READY [MUMBLES]
FOR CLIFF RESCUE.

34:58.226 --> 34:59.488
-COAST GUARD:
ROGER, COMMENCE VOICE.

35:01.360 --> 35:02.926
-PILOT: SWIMMER'S
OUTSIDE THE AIRCRAFT.

35:07.714 --> 35:08.976
SWIMMER'S GOING DOWN.

35:16.375 --> 35:19.334
SWIMMER'S 15 FEET
BELOW THE AIRCRAFT.

35:22.729 --> 35:25.993
SWIMMER'S 30 FEET
BELOW THE AIRCRAFT.

35:33.957 --> 35:36.569
BULWARK IS RIGHT, 40 FEET.

35:44.751 --> 35:46.535
RIGHT 10 FEET.

35:48.233 --> 35:49.234
EASY.

35:49.843 --> 35:50.844
HOLD.

35:52.454 --> 35:53.977
SWIMMER'S AT THE MAN.

35:54.630 --> 35:56.545
SWIMMER'S CONNECTING
THE RESCUE DEVICE.

36:09.993 --> 36:11.430
-PILOT: I HAVE A THUMB'S UP.

36:11.560 --> 36:12.779
PREPARE TO TAKE THE LOAD.

36:12.909 --> 36:13.867
-MAN: TAKING LOAD.

36:16.652 --> 36:18.219
-PILOT: SWIMMER AND
SURVIVOR ARE AWAY.

36:18.350 --> 36:20.003
CLEAR TO MOVE BACK AND LEFT.

36:20.656 --> 36:22.092
SWIMMER AND SURVIVOR
ARE COMING UP.

36:35.889 --> 36:37.891
SWIMMER AND SURVIVOR
ARE AT THE AIRCRAFT.

36:42.374 --> 36:45.420
-CB RADIO: LALB THIS
IS 6518, VOICE COMPLETE.

36:45.551 --> 36:46.813
WE ARE TRANSPORTING THE PRISONER

36:46.943 --> 36:48.641
TO MALIBU SUBSTATION.

38:02.018 --> 38:02.932
-I DON'T KNOW--

38:03.063 --> 38:04.020
-DON'T.

38:04.760 --> 38:07.023
DON'T SAY ANYTHING, PLEASE.

38:07.807 --> 38:09.852
-I JUST, I HAD TO SEE YOU.

38:09.983 --> 38:12.638
I HAVE TO LET YOU
KNOW HOW SORRY I AM!

38:12.768 --> 38:14.814
-NO!
IT'S YOUR FAULT!

38:15.771 --> 38:16.946
IT'S ALL YOUR FAULT!

38:17.077 --> 38:19.166
[ARGUING]

38:19.297 --> 38:20.210
-SHERRI!

38:20.950 --> 38:22.343
SHERRI!

38:22.474 --> 38:23.388
SHERRI, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,

38:23.518 --> 38:24.476
COME HERE, COME HERE.

38:24.606 --> 38:27.217
-NO, WHY DID SHE? [SOBBING]

38:32.658 --> 38:34.486
-SHERRI, I'M SORRY, I...

38:37.924 --> 38:39.055
SHERRI.

38:46.280 --> 38:47.368
-NO.

38:49.631 --> 38:50.502
NO.

38:59.162 --> 39:00.338
HE'S DEAD.

39:03.384 --> 39:04.559
-WE FOUND HIS
BODY THIS MORNING.

39:04.690 --> 39:10.348
[SOBBING]

39:11.871 --> 39:13.133
-I'M SO SORRY.

39:18.791 --> 39:23.404
[SOBBING]

39:53.129 --> 39:55.218
-EXCUSE ME, MITCH? ALEX?

39:55.349 --> 39:57.351
-HI.
-HEY, UM,

39:58.091 --> 39:59.788
I DID SOMETHING REALLY STUPID.

40:00.615 --> 40:02.878
THAT GUY THAT WAS THE CLIFF,

40:04.184 --> 40:05.490
HE WAS MY BOYFRIEND.

40:07.100 --> 40:08.667
-YOU REALLY WERE STUCK, HUH?

40:10.756 --> 40:14.020
-WE, WELL, HE STOLE A
CAR AND I WAS WITH HIM

40:14.150 --> 40:15.456
AND WE GOT CAUGHT.

40:15.587 --> 40:18.241
I WAS UNDER 18 SO
I GOT PROBATION.

40:18.938 --> 40:20.330
I THOUGHT I SHOULD TELL Y'ALL.

40:21.419 --> 40:23.159
-I'M GLAD YOU DID.

40:23.290 --> 40:26.162
-SO I GUESS THAT MEANS ROOKIE
SCHOOL'S OVER FOR ME, HUH?

40:30.776 --> 40:32.342
-WELL, IF YOU WERE UNDER 18,

40:32.473 --> 40:34.257
THE ARREST WON'T
BE ON YOUR RECORD,

40:34.388 --> 40:36.651
SO IT'S NOT A FACTOR
WITH THE COUNTY.

40:37.478 --> 40:38.436
-WHAT?

40:39.698 --> 40:41.047
-YOU'RE STILL IN ROOKIE SCHOOL.

40:42.048 --> 40:42.831
-THANK YOU.

40:42.962 --> 40:43.876
THANKS.

40:44.006 --> 40:45.051
-SURE.

40:45.791 --> 40:49.925
-I DO NEED UH, THREE CALL
CARS AND TWO TRUCKS WASHED.

40:50.056 --> 40:51.405
I'M LOOKING FOR SOME VOLUNTEERS.

40:52.058 --> 40:52.972
-I'M ON IT.

40:53.799 --> 40:54.843
-ALL RIGHT, GO ON.

40:56.802 --> 40:58.586
-WELL, YOU HANDLED
THAT ALL RATHER WELL.

40:58.717 --> 40:59.848
-MITCH: I THOUGHT SO.

41:02.198 --> 41:04.810
-I DON'T MIND GIVING
CREDIT WHERE CREDIT'S DUE.

41:06.420 --> 41:08.117
YOU KNOW, THIS KIND
OF REMINDS ME OF

41:08.248 --> 41:10.076
THAT LAST SCENE IN CASABLANCA.
-REALLY?

41:10.206 --> 41:11.512
-YOU KNOW THE ONE
WHERE CLAUDE RAINES

41:11.643 --> 41:12.600
SAYS TO HUMPHREY BOGART,

41:12.731 --> 41:13.775
"THIS COULD BE THE BEGINNING

41:13.906 --> 41:14.689
"OF A BEAUTIFUL FRIENDSHIP."

41:14.820 --> 41:15.777
-OH.

41:16.430 --> 41:17.649
EXCUSE ME, HOLD
THIS FOR A SECOND.

41:17.779 --> 41:19.041
I DON'T THINK SO.

41:23.785 --> 41:24.960
HEY HEY HEY!

41:27.833 --> 41:29.138
WHAT ARE YOU LAUGHING AT?

41:29.269 --> 41:33.839
[SHOUTING]

41:44.763 --> 41:49.507
[UPBEAT MUSIC]
